│ flag.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The `foldICmpWithMinMax()` function doesn't account for the `samesign`          │
│ attribute of icmp instructions. The standard min/max folding logic assumes regular comparison semantics, but     │
│ `samesign` introduces poison semantics when operands have different signs. This makes the standard               │
│ transformations unsafe because they don't consider when the comparison would produce poison versus a concrete    │
│ boolean value.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Points(s): Add a guard clause at the beginning of `foldICmpWithMinMax()` to   │
